What is Ansible?

Ansible is an automation and configuration management tool used in DevOps to automate server setup, application deployment, and system configuration.

It works without installing agents on servers (agentless) and connects using SSH.

🔧 Why DevOps Engineers Use Ansible

Automate server configuration

Install software automatically

Deploy applications

Manage multiple servers at the same time

Reduce manual work


🧠 Simple Example

Instead of logging into 10 servers and installing Docker manually:

Server1 → install docker
Server2 → install docker
Server3 → install docker

With Ansible, you run one command and it installs Docker on all servers automatically.

=================================================================================================

# Install Ansible
sudo dnf install ansible -y

# Verify installation
ansible --version

# Create project folder
mkdir ansible-project
cd ansible-project

# Create inventory file
cat <<EOF > inventory
[webservers]
localhost ansible_connection=local
EOF

# Create Ansible playbook
cat <<EOF > install-docker.yml
---
- name: Install Docker using Ansible
  hosts: webservers
  become: yes

  tasks:
    - name: Install Docker package
      dnf:
        name: docker
        state: present

    - name: Start Docker service
      service:
        name: docker
        state: started
        enabled: yes
EOF

# Run Ansible playbook
ansible-playbook -i inventory install-docker.yml

# Check Docker installation
docker --version
